Recovery Steps -Device Replacement with ID Authentication-
- Data Backup with ID Authentication 1. From the DigiTown screen on the current device, select Menu ⇒ Account Transfer ⇒ Account Transfer with ID Authentication ⇒ Data Backup with ID Authentication. Select a method to authenticate with, and tap "Yes" when prompted to backup. *Your browser or another app will open to authenticate your ID.
2. Your device browser or screen will activate, and the ID Authentication screen will be displayed. Sign in to the account you want to use to backup data.
3. The confirmation screen will be displayed. Select "Yes" to finalize authentication.
*Please sign in to an account you manage. There is a risk of transfer failure, or having your game taken over if another person's account is used.
- Data Recovery with ID Authentication 1. Install Digimon ReArise on the new device.
2. Tap the Transfer/Support button on the Title Screen. Select Account Transfer ⇒ Account Transfer with ID Authentication ⇒ Data Recovery with ID Authentication. Select the ID you have the data backed up to, and tap "Yes" when prompted to recover data. *Your browser or another app will open to sync your ID.
3. Your device browser or app will activate, and the ID Authentication screen will be displayed. Sign in to the account you want to use to backup data.
4. Digimon ReArise will activate and will prompt you to recover data. Tap "Yes".
*Verify the Tamer Level and Tamer Name of the data being recovered. *Data Recovery can be done through the Account Transfer section found within the Menu in the DigiTown screen.
Recovery Steps -Device Replacement with ID/Password-
- Issuing Password for Device Replacement 1. From the DigiTown screen on the current device, select Menu ⇒ Account Transfer ⇒ Account Transfer through ID/Password and tap the Issue Password button.
2. Your User ID and Your Password will be displayed. Please note and store this information in a safe place.
*If you forget to take a note of them, you can have a new password issued. If a new password is issued, the old password will become invalid.
- Inputting your Password 1. Install Digimon ReArise on the new device.
2. On the Title screen, tap the Transfer/Support button, then Account Transfer ⇒ Transfer with ID/Password, then input your User ID and Password.
3. The completion screen will be displayed once your data has been recovered. Verify the Tamer Level and Tamer Name on this screen.
4. Data Recovery can also be done through the Account Transfer section found within the Menu on the DigiTown screen.
Important Notice Regarding Transfer
1. DigiRubies cannot be transferred between devices of a different OS. Spending the DigiRubies prior to data transfer is recommended. DigiWalk progress will not be transferred. Rewards found in DigiWalk will not be transferred if not claimed.
2. Do not share your issued password with another individual or party. The admin team is not responsible for any loss incurred by doing this.
3. Issued passwords are valid for 90 days from the date of issue. Validity is reset each time a new password is issued. Only the most recently issued password will be valid.
4. Validity of a password will be nullified once used.
5. ID/Password transfer cannot be used if your data has been backed up with ID Authentication.
6. Only one account on one device is recommended for this app. Please refrain from using multiple accounts on one device, as it can result in data loss that cannot be restored.
7. You cannot sync multiple IDs.
8. ID Authentication with Apple ID can only be performed with devices running iOS 13.0 or newer.

Michi's Partner Digimon. Just as bright
and chatty as Michi, together they've
got all the bite to back up their bark.

A high school senior who keeps to

He tends to keep a cool head and
assess a situation before taking action.
The bond he shares with Dorumon is
unmatched. Incidentally, he happens
to be very talented at basketball.

Takumi's Partner Digimon. Fiercely loyal

in truth it wants to join in on
Herissmon and Salamon's fun deep down.

A shy and introverted college freshman
that plays in a big band jazz group.
He likes his alone time, but Elecmon
hardly gives him the pleasure. He often
pushes himself to avoid being a burden
to others.

Keito's childlike and free-spirited
Partner Digimon. Wherever Keito is,
Elecmon is sure to follow, hoping to get
spoiled by Keito. Elecmon places a lot of
trust in Keito's intelligence and believes
no opponent is a match for Keito's brain
and its own brawn.

A gentle and reserved college freshman,
Mayu's compassion sometimes gets her
caught up in sticky situations, causing
her partner Kudamon to worry about her
constantly. When it comes to her baking
hobby, she has a surprisingly laser-sharp
focus.

Mayu's Partner Digimon. On top of being
refined and cultured, the calm and
collected Kudamon keeps the absent-
minded Mayu grounded. Kudamon believes
Mayu's pastries are the best in the world
and won't let anyone say otherwise.

An innocent, mysterious creature who
appeared before you, possessing little to
no knowledge of the Real World. The
trials and tribulations with you cause
Herissmon to learn and grow as a Digimon.
A true Partner in every sense of the

any and all foes.

A very happy-go-lucky Digimon. Agumon
befriended Herissmon after helping them
fight some Spirals. Known to have an
insatiable appetite.

Mysterious entities that started to
materialize in the real world. They
resemble Digimon at first glance, but
their origins and motivations are unknown.
They are defined by the type of Digimon

A friendly third grader known for her carefree smile. In contrast to her shy brother Keito, Nozomi is an energetic girl that takes on all challenges with an adventurous spirit. She's taken a liking to an old-school handheld game she found at home, and can always be seen playing it.

Nozomi's partner Digimon that loves playing and having fun more than anything. In contrast to its appearance, it's actually an Ultimate Digimon. Nozomi and Pumpkinmon act like best friends, and play together often.

The owner of Cafe Truffle. The main characters often meet up at her cafe, so she's come to know the Tamers well. She watches over them and their Digimon, sometimes with kindness, other times a harsh word or two.
Chihiro's partner Digimon, found outside the cafe on a rainy day. Its cuteness is a cut above, making it hard to view Lopmon as the old-fashioned and serious Digimon that it is.

A mysterious girl appears before you suddenly.

A Digimon that appeared along with Mon.

A high school student who always charges at things full-speed ahead.
An underclassman one year younger than Takumi in the same basketball club,
he respects Takumi more than anyone else.
He has a straightforward, honest-to-a-fault personality that sometimes gets him into trouble,

Kazuma Natsuyagi's Partner Digimon. It was born from a DigiEgg which Kazuma protected from Spirals.
